   686	**Deviation from the pre-implementation draft (impl review round 1 finding 3):** an earlier draft of this index also included `test_subscribe_empty_batch_after_timeout`, asserting the empty-batch shape that chapter 7 §6.2 describes for quiescent subscribes. During implementation the citation check (§I) flagged the citation as non-MUST: chapter 7 §6.2 makes both the timeout window (RECOMMENDED 30s — a SHOULD) and the empty-batch response shape descriptive rather than normative MUSTs. The test was dropped under the "MUSTs only" rule from chapter 9 §3 rather than re-cited to a stretchy ancestor MUST. If a future spec amendment elevates the empty-batch shape to a MUST, the scenario should be restored.
