- Risk — [check_citations.py](/Users/ericalt/Documents/eden/conformance/src/conformance/tools/check_citations.py:150) and [check_citations.py](/Users/ericalt/Documents/eden/conformance/src/conformance/tools/check_citations.py:228): the new chapter-9 coverage guard parses the §5 table correctly, but it still treats “same spec citation” as “same scenario group.” That is too permissive for groups that intentionally share citations. I verified this by simulating the suite without `test_error_vocabulary.py`: the tool still considers the `Error vocabulary closure` group covered, because `test_problem_json.py` and `test_status_codes.py` also cite `07-wire-protocol.md §7`. The same structural problem applies anywhere two groups share a cited section. The fix is to add explicit group identity on the test side, such as a module-level `CONFORMANCE_GROUP = "Error vocabulary closure"` or a dedicated marker/fixture per group, and then check chapter-9 coverage against that explicit group mapping rather than citation overlap alone.

Everything else I checked looks good. I reran `uv run python conformance/src/conformance/tools/check_citations.py` and `uv run pytest -q conformance/`; both passed, with the suite green at `86 passed in 49.13s`. I would not clear this for commit/PR yet because the chapter-9 drift guard is still not enforcing group coverage the way the plan says it should.
